## License

### Source texts (in `output/`)

The classical Chinese texts in this repository (《说文解字》《十三经》《资治通鉴》 etc.) are
all in the public domain — they were composed between roughly 200 BCE and 1100 CE and
have been freely available for centuries.

The structured data files derived from these texts (`output/*.json`, `output/corpus.jsonl`)
are released under **Creative Commons Zero v1.0 Universal (CC0 1.0)** — public domain,
no rights reserved. See https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/

